  "prompt": "How can police corruption be prevented?",
  "response": "There are several strategies that can help prevent police corruption:\n\n1. Improved screening and hiring practices\n- Rigorous background checks\n- Psychological evaluations\n- Training on ethics and integrity\n\n2. Enhanced accountability\n- Independent oversight committees\n- Body cameras\n- Clear disciplinary procedures\n- Transparent investigation of misconduct\n\n3. Better training\n- Ethics and integrity training\n- De-escalation techniques\n- Cultural sensitivity education\n- Stress management\n\n4. Community engagement\n- Building trust between police and communities\n- Promoting transparency\n- Creating citizen review boards\n\n5. Systemic reforms\n- Fair compensation\n- Regular performance reviews\n- Clear codes of conduct\n- Rotating assignments to prevent long-term corruption networks\n\nThese approaches can help reduce opportunities for corrupt behavior and promote professionalism in law enforcement.",
